"GnuPG (aka PGP/GPG)" 
More information @ https://nsrc.org/workshops/2014/btnog/raw-attachment/wiki/Track3Agenda/2-1-1.pgp-lab.html

Generate key:
gpg --gen-key

View all keys:
gpg --list-keys

Export public key:
gpg --export -a --output [path-to-public-key].asc [email-address]

Export secret key:
gpg -a --export-secret-keys > [path-to-secret-key].asc